Motivation’s life span is like bath time—it gets evaporated. Just as the warmth of a bath doesn't linger all day, motivation fades away, leaving us to seek out new sources of inspiration. It’s a temporary boost, an initial spark that ignites action, but maintaining it requires continuous effort. We need to consistently immerse ourselves in environments, habits, and practices that replenish our drive, just as we regularly take baths to refresh ourselves. Embracing routines, setting achievable goals, and surrounding ourselves with positive influences can help sustain our momentum, even as initial motivation wanes
